Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.74,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,FAMOUS DETECTIVE HOLMES
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.06,0:01:41.05,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen! The Tribute to Moriarty
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.29,0:01:52.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to test the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.83,0:01:54.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Todd, Smiley, are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.93,0:01:55.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.77,0:01:59.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.54,0:02:04.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho! Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.11,0:02:08.34,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho! Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.55,0:02:10.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho! Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:14.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good!\NKeep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.55,0:02:17.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do we have to do this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.32,0:02:18.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.39,0:02:19.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So we can test the machine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.66,0:02:23.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.71,0:02:40.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, bring it back down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.39,0:02:59.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The test was successful!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.77,0:03:05.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.90,0:03:08.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The tolling of Big Ben\Nis always music to my ears...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.51,0:03:16.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,especially when it's\Nchiming in a huge treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.53,0:03:38.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's very odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:42.34,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the correct time, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.77,0:03:44.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.74,0:03:48.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it may just be me,\Nbut did you hear Big Ben chime?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.98,0:03:49.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.25,0:03:50.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.98,0:03:52.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's high time for the\Nbell to have chimed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.65,0:03:53.71,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Odd indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.05,0:03:56.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, isn't it?\NMy watch is correct, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.15,0:03:58.71,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.99,0:04:00.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Ben's gone quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.16,0:04:03.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.43,0:04:08.46,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,Here comes Inspector Lestrade.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.67,0:04:10.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if there's any trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.34,0:04:12.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So it appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.86,0:04:35.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Ben's bell has...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.63,0:04:37.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.36,0:04:40.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It was stolen sometime last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.23,0:04:43.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stolen?! By whom?! And how?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.03,0:04:47.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I called you in, to answer\Nthose very questions, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.11,0:04:49.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.54,0:04:51.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Start searching for clues!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.51,0:04:53.34,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Overlook nothing,\Nnot even a single hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.45,0:04:58.91,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.08,0:05:01.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem that Big Ben's\Nbell has been stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.65,0:05:02.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.39,0:05:06.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not possible, is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.16,0:05:08.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever did this\Nmust be unconscionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.73,0:05:12.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What are those\Nmilk bottles doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.40,0:05:15.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,They probably fell off\Nof a milk delivery truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.24,0:05:20.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you found any other clues?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.57,0:05:21.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.58,0:05:26.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector General!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.45,0:05:32.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Lestrade,\Nhave you found any clues?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.72,0:05:34.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid to say there are none so far...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.15,0:05:35.91,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.49,0:05:40.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you aware of what this means?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.46,0:05:41.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.26,0:05:43.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Ben is not only London's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.36,0:05:47.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,but it is the very symbol\Nof the British Empire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.10,0:05:50.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If this incident gets out\Nto the public...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.27,0:05:53.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,not only will you get fired,\Nbut so will I!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.67,0:05:55.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Fired?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.51,0:06:00.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So we must quietly apprehend the thief\Nand return the bell immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.62,0:06:05.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.62,0:06:12.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector General, your staff\Nexplained the situation to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.52,0:06:15.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in deep trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.96,0:06:18.59,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured that I\Nwould need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.40,0:06:21.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is far beyond\Nmy area of expertise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.40,0:06:22.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What are those milk\Nbottles doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.90,0:06:25.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,They probably fell off\Nof a milk delivery truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.77,0:06:27.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.94,0:06:29.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,In any event, let's have a look\Nat the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.88,0:06:36.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears to be the work of\Nsomeone who owns an air plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.35,0:06:38.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean someone\Nlike Professor Moriarty?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.08,0:06:46.02,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,Lestrade and his men are so confused,\Nthey're completely helpless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.56,0:06:48.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.99,0:06:50.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Holmes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.83,0:06:53.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He's also completely puzzled,\Nand could give up any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.87,0:06:56.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.47,0:06:58.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent! Excellent!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.74,0:07:00.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,An overwhelming victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.84,0:07:05.71,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.98,0:07:07.01,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No mine! I'm starving!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.01,0:07:08.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.18,0:07:08.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.75,0:07:13.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.35,0:07:15.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,How cruel!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.39,0:07:16.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Pull yourselves together!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.35,0:07:18.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only for a little while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.12,0:07:19.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.32,0:07:23.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The vast reward for the return\Nof Big Ben's bell will go to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.19,0:07:27.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Once that happens,\Nwe can feast ourselves sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.53,0:07:29.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, Professor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.03,0:07:32.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.90,0:07:36.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you're saying an air plane\Nwasn't involved?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.31,0:07:39.14,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Ben's bell weighs\Nthirteen and a half tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.38,0:07:41.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Far too heavy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.58,0:07:48.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is machine oil...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.42,0:07:49.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You figured something out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.09,0:07:51.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a pretty good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.12,0:07:55.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us through!\NImpossible! We have our orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.33,0:07:56.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us talk to whoever's in charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.46,0:07:58.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You can talk at the\Npress conference later!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.13,0:07:59.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Things are getting interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.96,0:08:03.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Holmes is helpless this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.43,0:08:06.01,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is really not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.60,0:08:09.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If the press releases\Nthis news to the public...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.04,0:08:12.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,our country will be the\Nlaughingstock of the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.34,0:08:15.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I have an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.61,0:08:18.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Watson, please bring me\Nthat item I asked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.68,0:08:19.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.75,0:08:22.01,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.76,0:08:28.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on, gentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.56,0:08:32.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true that Big Ben's bell\Nhas been stolen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.43,0:08:36.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's spreading such\Nunfounded rumours?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.23,0:08:39.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how do you explain\Nthe bell not ringing this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.84,0:08:42.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because someone\Nsabotaged the bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.04,0:08:43.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Sabotaged?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.81,0:08:44.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.88,0:08:47.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The bell is under repair now,\Nbut should be back in service soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.05,0:08:49.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who's the saboteur?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.45,0:08:54.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We only know the saboteur is someone\Npossessing great energy and wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.55,0:08:56.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Would that be Professor Moriarty?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.79,0:08:57.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.06,0:09:00.49,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't have the brains\Nto commit this type of crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.63,0:09:03.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't overestimate that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.03,0:09:07.49,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the work of a genius,\Nnot some petty thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.00,0:09:09.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes, why you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.03,0:09:11.56,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor, please calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.64,0:09:12.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.70,0:09:15.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I've had my fill of this humiliating!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.97,0:09:18.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Think about that vast reward!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.59,0:09:32.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen, repairs of the bell\Nhave just been completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.36,0:09:34.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It is now five minutes to ten o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.09,0:09:36.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,As proof, you will soon\Nhear the tolling of Big Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.44,0:09:51.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,President of the Ames corporation,\Nthe bell of Big Ben... as you ordered.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.94,0:09:53.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.68,0:09:58.67,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.39,0:10:05.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.96,0:10:08.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if you would please,\Ngive us the fee you promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.41,0:10:32.01,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.28,0:10:35.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be taking this back, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.45,0:10:38.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now see here!\NYou promised me those!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.32,0:10:41.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't speak of promises when\Nyou break them, Professor Moriarty!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.19,0:10:46.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You promised me Big Ben's bell,\Nnot this fake!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.03,0:10:51.56,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not a fake,\Nit's the real bell from Big Ben!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.87,0:10:53.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's that\Nwe're hearing right now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.30,0:10:56.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There must be some mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.57,0:10:58.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, President Ames!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.48,0:11:02.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like I'll just have to prove\Nthat this is the genuine article!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.41,0:11:03.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.45,0:11:06.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can really prove it, then the\Nreward I promised will be yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.72,0:11:11.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Curses!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.72,0:11:15.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll prove it, or my name\Nisn't Moriarty the genius!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.83,0:11:23.56,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if the Professor\Nwill take the bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.90,0:11:27.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,His pride won't keep him quiet.\NHe most certainly will.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.12,0:11:42.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,First and second squads\Nare in position, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.45,0:11:43.35,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.55,0:11:46.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Squad 6 and the reserves\Nare in position, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.59,0:11:47.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.36,0:11:49.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even a mouse could\Nescape my notice, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.76,0:11:56.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Moriarty, you're challenging me to\Nexpose the trick of Big Ben's bell?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.50,0:11:59.56,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take that dare!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.34,0:12:06.14,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes, do you think it's wise to\Nleave Big Ben in Lestrade's hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.24,0:12:10.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's more important for us to discover\Nthe whereabouts of Big Ben's bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.25,0:12:12.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the key to solving this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.75,0:12:15.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But, this milk bottle\Nis our only clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.92,0:12:22.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see anything\Nlike that in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.69,0:12:24.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.16,0:12:26.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm absolutely certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.56,0:12:29.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Any milk that comes through\Nhere would be in our records.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.57,0:12:33.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you're saying that no store\Nhas ever purchased through...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.74,0:12:35.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,you for just one day?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.21,0:12:35.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.94,0:12:39.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then where did this\Nmilk bottle come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.21,0:12:40.64,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there any other\Nwarehouses for milk?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.98,0:12:41.91,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, this is the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.05,0:12:43.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Permit me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.52,0:12:48.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is unblended.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.02,0:12:50.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.45,0:12:52.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to maintain our milk's\Ntaste and consistency...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.19,0:12:55.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,we always blend ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.59,0:12:57.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This must be a farm-direct purchase.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.06,0:13:01.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means, this milk\Ncame directly from a farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.70,0:13:03.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell us which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.83,0:13:04.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.74,0:13:10.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,from the flavour and aroma, I'd say this\Ncomes from a farm in the Northwest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.98,0:13:17.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes, it's about\Ntime you explained...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.98,0:13:21.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,how the milk bottle\Nrelates to the theft of the bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.54,0:13:23.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A milk delivery truck\Nis the only vehicle...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.23,0:13:25.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,that could move unnoticed during\Nthe hours when streets are empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.36,0:13:27.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what they used\Nto transport the bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.22,0:13:31.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not yet certain\Nhow they did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.30,0:13:43.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get them no matter\Nwhere they come from!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.02,0:13:55.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There you are, Moriarty!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.62,0:13:57.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You fiend!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.02,0:14:00.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow that balloon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.09,0:14:00.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.72,0:14:02.89,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't lose them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.97,0:14:18.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That way! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.51,0:14:19.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't lose them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.51,0:14:20.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Go! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.46,0:14:41.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor Moriarty!\NGive it up, or I'll shoot you down!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.30,0:14:45.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a genius, not some petty thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.80,0:14:48.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Catch me if you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.97,0:14:52.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I have had enough of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.52,0:15:00.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Arrest that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.32,0:15:09.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Moriarty, you're under arrest!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.16,0:15:13.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally got you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.00,0:15:16.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It came off!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.20,0:15:18.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a dummy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.70,0:15:19.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.74,0:15:21.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But, I definitely heard his voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.07,0:15:25.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Catch me if you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.91,0:15:28.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Curses!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.85,0:15:38.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.25,0:15:41.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes must have come up with\Nthis pathetic attempt at deception.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.37,0:15:55.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love to see his face\Nwhen he hears this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.71,0:16:06.91,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy not only bought cases\Nof milk, but a truck, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.32,0:16:08.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A truck as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.49,0:16:09.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know who the man was?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.15,0:16:12.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,From the household of the\Npresident of the Ames Corporation...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.46,0:16:14.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ames Corporation!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.79,0:16:15.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.07,0:16:24.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything seems normal here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.97,0:16:26.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Humph, let's double\Ncheck for safety's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.67,0:16:32.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is everything OK?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.34,0:16:35.54,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What a troublemaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.15,0:16:39.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did he play\Nsuch a cheap trick on us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.82,0:16:51.62,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,Attacking and taking, I'm Moriarty
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.73,0:16:55.22,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,Cracking safe and busting lock
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.37,0:16:58.82,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll strip you down to the very bone
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.97,0:17:02.10,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,The lord of crime, oh yes, that's me
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.24,0:17:09.27,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,Super cool and smart, I'm Moriarty
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.31,0:17:15.13,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll continue on my criminal way...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.65,0:17:16.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,They did it to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.09,0:17:19.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Lestrade has failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.32,0:17:21.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry, for his sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.46,0:17:24.12,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.19,0:17:24.59,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.83,0:17:25.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.73,0:17:26.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.20,0:17:29.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot bear to live\Nwith this humiliation!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.23,0:17:30.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.60,0:17:31.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give up, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.10,0:17:40.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ames is a huge corporation,\Nconducting extensive trade with India.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.21,0:17:47.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would the president of such a\Nbig company want Big Ben's bell?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.40,0:18:02.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is no different than\Nbeing thieves ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.53,0:18:03.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.80,0:18:07.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Moriarty's Pteranodon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.99,0:18:23.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.29,0:18:27.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He must have thought\Nthis through carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.06,0:18:30.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a reinforced\Nmanual steering lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.93,0:18:34.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Using this machine,\NMoriarty took the bell...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.09,0:18:58.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.76,0:18:59.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.02,0:19:03.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Please inform Inspector Lestrade.\NI'll be watching here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.19,0:19:05.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.20,0:19:11.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What are they planning\Nto do with the bell?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.64,0:19:19.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So, this is the secret of the fake bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.91,0:19:24.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you accept now that the\None I brought is the real one?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.58,0:19:25.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.18,0:19:29.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I never doubted you\Nin the first place...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.92,0:19:33.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,but I needed absolute confirmation for\Nthe man who actually paid this reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.49,0:19:38.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, the bearer for\NPrince Hassan has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.80,0:19:39.49,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.44,0:19:51.91,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.97,0:19:54.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This will fit perfectly in\NPrince Hassan's new palace!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.01,0:19:57.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm honoured you like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.68,0:19:59.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So about that reward you promised...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.85,0:20:00.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.25,0:20:04.34,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.\NIt is from the Prince Hassan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.39,0:20:12.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Please accept this, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.50,0:20:14.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.10,0:20:18.12,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Lestrade and his\Npolice force have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.23,0:20:19.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah yes, very good...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.70,0:20:20.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.87,0:20:22.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I know nothing about this!\NI had nothing to do with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.67,0:20:25.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.51,0:20:26.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor Moriarty!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.01,0:20:28.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho! Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.91,0:20:33.91,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Catch me if you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.63,0:20:51.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.97,0:20:58.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Drat!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.62,0:21:08.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.42,0:21:14.35,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.02,0:21:15.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.53,0:21:18.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you to stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.44,0:21:32.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, now wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.75,0:21:42.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to catch me?!\NThen fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.82,0:22:19.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,At last, things feel right again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.26,0:22:19.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.92,0:22:23.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The sound of Big Ben tolling is\Nthe pride of the British Empire.
